But with perfect defense moves Yoshizawa killed white hops
At this point, Nakamura understood that he cannot win.
And he began to re-organize his material, for defense purpose
Now, he had wasted all his power,
Hard to tell, was Yoshizawa wiser in this game or luckier,
but by the 36th move, black reached its tactics goal.
The position was safe, under the control, enough space to develop, and black's tempo.
It was all that Yoshizawa needed.
